<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="931" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d931">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Eddy</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-04"><hi rend="italic">October 4,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Adee states that if Miss Stone is held in Turkey, Mr. Eddy is to
                            bring to the attention of the Turkish Government the facts in relation
                            to the abduction and the very great importance the United States
                            Government attaches to her safe deliverance from the brigands; to
                            request the aid of the Turkish Government and impress upon it the
                            extreme gravity of the affair.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>